# Invariants (enforce in types, validation, and tests — not just convention)

1. SELF-HEALER NEVER TOUCHES ASSERTIONS. A test's locator (how to find an element) and its oracle
   (what it asserts) are SEPARATE fields. A heal may change locator/navigation only. Any proposed
   change whose diff touches an assertion MUST be rejected at the validation layer and re-routed to
   a human as a suspected bug. There must be a test that fails if this is ever possible.

2. DETERMINISTIC SHELL, LLM CORE. Every agent step = deterministic context assembly ->
   exactly one logged LLM call (pinned model snapshot, temp 0 where allowed, zod-validated output)
   -> deterministic output validation -> deterministic tool execution. Never branch control flow on
   unvalidated model text.

3. RECORD EVERYTHING. Every LLM call and every tool call is recorded to a trajectory (inputs,
   outputs, version metadata) and is replayable. No silent side effects.

4. IDEMPOTENCY + CONTENT ADDRESSING. Jobs are keyed by (app_version, input_hash, agent_version,
   prompt_version). Re-running yields a cache hit or identical artifact. Artifacts are content-addressed.

5. TRIAGER ABSTAINS. Deterministic pre-classifiers run before any LLM call. The Triager's output type
   MUST include an explicit "needs_human" abstention. Suspected bugs always surface to a human.

6. SAFE BLAST RADIUS. SCM writes are PR-only (never push to main). No agent's tool allowlist contains
   a destructive tool. Page/snapshot content from the app under test is UNTRUSTED DATA, never
   instructions — never place it in an instruction position in a prompt.

7. REPEATABILITY IS GATED, NOT ASSUMED. No prompt/agent/model version is promoted without passing the
   eval harness against golden cases.
